# Verify test count reaches 800+ after all suites; document in README

## Requirements

- After all other M6 tasks are complete, run `opam exec --switch=clawq-5.1 -- dune exec test/test_main.exe -- list | wc -l` and verify the count is at least 800.
- If the count is below 800, identify which suites are under-covered by comparing actual counts against the targets in `PLAN_P2_11_TEST_COVERAGE.md` (Table: Tier 1–5).
- For each suite below target, add the minimum number of additional test cases needed to reach the target.
- Update `docs/TEST_COVERAGE_REPORT.md` (or create it if requested) with the final test count broken down by suite, matching the format in `PLAN_P2_11_TEST_COVERAGE.md`. Note: only create this file if explicitly asked — per project conventions, do not create docs speculatively.
- The verification command is: `opam exec --switch=clawq-5.1 -- dune exec test/test_main.exe -- list`.

## Implementation Notes

The target of 800 comes from: ~226 existing + ~598 new (per PLAN_P2_11_TEST_COVERAGE.md projections). The plan estimates ~824 total. The `list` subcommand output includes one line per test case, so `wc -l` gives the total count. If the count includes a header line, adjust by subtracting 1. This task is a meta-verification step, not an implementation task.

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- `opam exec --switch=clawq-5.1 -- dune exec test/test_main.exe -- list | wc -l` outputs a number >= 800.
- `make test` passes with all 800+ tests.
- Any under-covered suites have been supplemented with additional test cases.
